<br>
1) Your group's damage is already very high, or melee makes up very little of the group damage (which allows you to either drop warsong or let Marr slip for the few seconds it takes to kill something).<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
2) Your group has plenty of healing power, but tank is perpetually in danger of dying before the heals land (which makes the extra AC do some good).<br>
<br>
In other words, I used it for Vxed/Tipt with &quot;marginal&quot; tanks (especially knights).  I'm not sure it is as worth it now that they've massive reduced the attack of the mobs there now.<br>
<br>
But if a tank requests it, I see no harm in finding a way to work it in.<br>
<br>
Also worth considering for 2 bard groups (perhaps in LDoN hard?), though not always the best choice.<br>
<br>
- Lall<br>
Bold Bardess with 113 Melodic Tools<br>
Shards of Avalon, Xegony. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cerezo>Cerezo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 774<br> <font color=#330000>(6/30/04 12:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19552.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Niv's</span><hr size=1> i usually do a resist (group or AE), niv's harmonic and cha.  no real need to do 4 song twist cuz i rather have no songs drop at any given time. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Times;font-size:medium;">Impresario</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Times;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120074" target="top">Cerezo EdgeWalker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
